                *** Char methods ***
Character.isLetter(ch);
Character.toLowerCase(ch)
Character.isLetterOrDigit(ch)


                *** REMEMBER ***

                *** Most important ***

PriorityQueue<Integer> pq = new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());

                Find second largest element:

       maxHeap.poll();              // remove largest
       int secondLargest = maxHeap.peek();

                        ******

Array has just property, it is not a function:
    length

String has it as function:
    length()



            *** Convert to a String array ***
        String[] array = collection.toArray(new String[collection.size()]);


            *** Cool map method ***

map.getOrDefault(key, defaultValue)

ðŸ‘‰ Meaning:
If key exists in the map â†’ return its value
If key does NOT exist â†’ return defaultValue (without adding it to the map)

            *** Compare Arrays ***

Arrays.equals(a, b)

            *** Note ***

There is no method to convert List<Integer> to int [] you have to do that :

int[] arr = list.stream()
                .mapToInt(Integer::intValue)
                .toArray();

